. Using String.valueOf()
java
Copy code
int number = 123;
String str = String.valueOf(number);
System.out.println(str); // Output: "123"
2. Using Integer.toString()
java
Copy code
int number = 123;
String str = Integer.toString(number);
System.out.println(str); // Output: "123"
3. Using String Concatenation
java
Copy code
int number = 123;
String str = number + ""; // Implicitly converts number to string
System.out.println(str); // Output: "123"
Python
1. Using str() Function
python
Copy code
number = 123
str_number = str(number)
print(str_number)  # Output: "123"
2. Using String Formatting
python
Copy code
number = 123
str_number = f"{number}"
print(str_number)  # Output: "123"
python
Copy code
number = 123
str_number = "{}".format(number)
print(str_number)  # Output: "123"
